--- title: Fastseq keywords: fastai sidebar: home_sidebar summary: "A way to use fastai with sequence data" ---

Installing¶

Please install fastai2 according to the instructions.

Then install Fastseq by:

pip install -e .

How to use¶

from fastai2.basics import *
from fastseq.all import *
from fastseq.nbeats.model import *
from fastseq.nbeats.learner import *

horizon, lookback = 5, 30
items = dummy_data_generator(60, 10, nrows=300)
data = TSDataLoaders.from_items(items,horizon = horizon, lookback = lookback, step=5,valid_pct=.2)

Train:1500; Valid: 300; Test 300

Getting the data fastai style:

path = untar_data(URLs.m4_daily)
data = TSDataLoaders.from_folder(path, horizon = horizon, lookback = lookback, nrows = 300, step=5, after_batch = NormalizeTS())

Train:43294; Valid: 600; Test 300

data.show_batch()

from fastai2.optimizer import *
mdl = NBeatsNet(device = data.train.device, stack_types=('trend','seasonality'), horizon=horizon, lookback=lookback)
learn = Learner(data, mdl, loss_func=F.mse_loss, opt_func= ranger)       

from fastai2.callback.all import *
learn.lr_find()       

learn.fit_flat_cos(1, 2e-4)
learn.recorder.plot_loss()
learn.recorder.plot_sched()
